The Waikoropupu River is a river of the Tasman Region of New Zealand's South Island. It flows generally northeast to reach the Takaka River close to the town of Takaka. "Place Name Detail: Waikoropupu River". New Zealand Geographic Placenames Database. Land Information New Zealand. http://www.linz.govt.nz/placenames/find-names/topographic-names-db/database/index.aspx?p=. Retrieved 12 July 2009. Coordinates: 4050S 17248E / 40.833S 172.8E / -40.833; 172.8
